        <updateDate>2022-10-20T17:17:35Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Prevent Family Fire Act of 2022</strong></p> <p>This bill allows a new business-related tax credit, through 2030, for 10% of the amount of&nbsp;the first retail sale of a safe firearm storage device. The amount upon which the credit is based may not exceed $400. </p> <p>A <em>safe firearm storage device</em> is a device that (1) is designed and marketed to deny unauthorized access to, or rendering inoperable, a firearm or ammunition; and (2) is secured by a combination lock, key lock, or lock based on biometric information.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
